text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
the church will never grasp the severity of abuse and the deceptive nature of leaders who abuse, until we take the time to listen to those who have experienced these horrors.
.
this will only happen if church leaders humble themselves and invite abuse survivors to their buildings to genuinely learn from them. it is time for church leaders to stop talking at survivors and start listening to them. we don't always need another sermon. we need church leaders who will listen. listening takes humility. preaching does not. pride can preach. we don't need another sermon. there's plenty out there. we need humble leaders who will listen to the real-life stories about what is wrong with the church today.
.
are there any church leaders out there willing to apply this?
.
.

text: parma, una grande coperta contro la violenza sulle donne la pavimentazione a ridosso della cattedrale di parma è stata "scaldata" da una coperta formata da 1300 quadrotti realizzati ai ferri o all’uncinetto di qualsiasi colore delle dimensioni di 50x50 uniti 4 a 4 con filo rosso. ogni pezzo è in vendita a un prezzo simbolico e il ricavato sarà utilizzato per l’acquisto di macchinari diagnostici per la prevenzione e la sorveglianza del rischio di carcinoma mammario e ovarico. l'iniziativa, promossa dall'associazione di parma la doppia elica, con il patrocinio del comune di parma, azienda ospedaliero universitaria e ausl, vede la partecipazione di viva vittoria – opera relazionale condivisa ha come ulteriore finalità quella di fermare la violenza sulle donne, con un progetto collettivo e condiviso lavorando a maglia insieme per lanciare un messaggio coinvolgente, aggregante e, nello stesso tempo, entusiasmante. raccolti dalla vendita 23mila euro. (foto marco vasini)  https://parma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2018/11/10/foto/parma_una_grande_coperta_contro_la_violenza_sulle_donne_-_foto-211255139/ anche #leguerrieresciencesartsandevents hanno contribuito alla realizzazione di questa grande iniziativa donando chili di lana all’ associazione #doppiaelica #cancroalseno #salute #nonmollaremai #metoo #breastcancerawareness

text:
@regrann from @the.gentleman.wolf -  men are biologically driven to try to impress the female and to feel needed in order to feel loved, but what most men fail to recognize is that a woman's greatest need is emotional intimacy and connection in order to be "in love" with him. unfortunately, this is the part of the relationship that most men struggle with, they just are not taught how to be emotionally available. why does this happen? usually, in the household, the mother takes care of her son, nurtures him, comforts him, feeds him and gives him affection and praise, while the father teaches him how to work, fix things, take care of business and "be a man." so when a man goes into a relationship, he often ends up confused. he's not used to someone coming to him for emotional support, he's used to his mother listening to him about his problems and taking care of his needs. he probably never saw his father sitting there, holding his mother, listening to her feelings and being empathetic. so then, he's taught that when a woman loves a man, she takes care of him and when a man loves a woman, he demonstrates his value by fixing things and solving problems. lack of emotional intimacy leads to lack of love, trust and satisfaction in a relationship and is why most relationships end. men, if you want her to be happy and satisfied with you, learn how to be emotionally available by listening, being in tune with her feelings, and by being supportive and consistent; her feelings are not something you can "fix." men also want to feel loved supported, try not to be overly critical or negative with him, but be supportive and reward him for what he's doing right in the relationship.
remember, a woman in love will do anything for you, but it's your job to do whatever it takes for her to be in love with you. -joel clemons • love, life & relationship coach @the.gentleman.wolf

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf
medium

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf
medium

text:
decolonial bizness world is a free and open method for business education that promotes reparations and decolonization. 
#reparations means repairing the damage that racism, capitalism, and settler colonialism have produced globally through formal, economic amends. 
#decolonization means creating open pathways for life to thrive on this planet as we move into the new sun. both reparations and decolonization involve abolishing borders and prisons and restoring the #sacred connections between humans and the many other forms of life that live on this planet, earth, as we face #climatechaos, the #sixthextinction, and #proudfascism.

#decolonialbiznessworld is made for #themagicians of the global economy, those of us who have been forced to the #margins of capitalist accumulation, while serving its masters and everyday beneficiaries. we have been made marginal even as we remain the global majority. decolonial bizness world is also made for our allies, for people who see truth through #delusion and violence and are willing to put their money where their #mantra lives: on the books and into daily sacred practice.

first, there is no one method or formula for determining reparations.

so much of the violence we experience is personalized. the violence we experience as individuals is always shared by other people and communities, yet how it affects us is embodied and related to who we are in this earth walk. that's why this method was designed for people like you and #metoo.

second, calculating reparations is always an economic and #spiritual practice.

above all, the spiritual dimension of this method is central, and survivors must lead each initiative. the point is to foster #healing, not pay for therapy and legal costs, and give people the support we require to #create #solutions for ourselves and our #beloved communities. so, what does healing mean for you as a #survivor of the violence you seek to stop? given your daily life and needs at this time, what do you need to put in place to #learn and apply the method?

from a purely economic perspective.... #42 #24 #242  #33 #gg #del #babyjail #hashtaghanging #delugefelicia #248whodoweexcoriate? #quadruplebycockroach

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
this post was originally going to focus on how people like #daisymarquez and #nikitadragun aren’t just #modeling cosmetics but creating business #models. but something happened. 
something like #rape, like #stalking, like #harassment. and i don’t just mean #metoo as a moment or a movement.

as i was #watching the channels of @daisymarquez_ and @nikita_dragun , i started to see how these young folks are using their videos as a #platform to #exposeviolence – and even document it as it unfolds. in one vid, for example, #daisy marquez describes three episodes of stalking in one night. we can hear the #terror in her #voice as she records the #events as they happen. #healing is #natural. violence isn’t. #mabrika. #expose. #welcometothefamilia. 
on nikita dragun’s channel, she speaks to the fear she often feels when people learn that she’s trans and how she protects herself in public. if you watch her archive, you can see that she’s modeling her evolution, her security protocol, and her expertise. like dragun’s makeup tutorials, her channel is an expert blend of reality as it now exists: danger and beautiful, creative existence.

yes, beauty videos can generate a revenue stream through advertisements. yes, they can enable makeup artists to land paid gigs at events, jobs at makeup counters, and even the much coveted corporate sponsorship. yet there’s more: their makers are speaking to reality and blending it with fantasy (and frosted shadows) to make life worth living.
name: darshan elena campos

this post was originally going to focus on how people like #daisymarquez and #nikitadragun aren’t just #modeling cosmetics but creating business #models. but something happened. 
something like #rape, like #stalking, like #harassment. and i don’t just mean #metoo as a moment or a movement.

as i was #watching the channels of @daisymarquez_ and @nikita_dragun , i started to see how these young folks are using their videos as a #platform to #exposeviolence – and even document it as it unfolds. in one vid, for example, #daisy marquez describes three episodes of stalking in one night. we can hear the #terror in her #voice as she records the #events as they happen. #healing is #natural. violence isn’t. #mabrika. #expose. #welcometothefamilia. 
on nikita dragun’s channel, she speaks to the fear she often feels when people learn that she’s trans and how she protects herself in public. if you watch her archive, you can see that she’s modeling her evolution, her security protocol, and her expertise. like dragun’s makeup tutorials, her channel is an expert blend of reality as it now exists: danger and beautiful, creative existence.

text:
i just watched a story on 60 minutes that has not only brought up some personal memories but has angered me. 
how our judicial system can block a victim of sexual abuse from telling her story for the rest of life is utter bullshit. but the disgusting excuse for a man is able to do interviews and gloat about the age gap between him and jane doe. 
how they can say that it was a consensual relationship is bullshit. she was 15 and he was 59.  she was underage plain and simple. 
i myself have been a victim of sexual assault and to be told i couldn't tell my story if i chose too. would have upset me. 
i myself haven't told alot of people about my past as i was scared people would judge me. but the #metoo movement has given me strength to talk about it in the hopes i can help other women to get through it too. i am now studying to be a counselor specializing in sexual assault. 
so lets get behind this young australian girl and give her a voice.

text:
сегодня должен быть 3ий день по плану. воспоминания о матери. должна признаться, всё готово, но вот выложить это.... не очень легко. да и написала я в этот раз много. вошла во вкус видимо, а может быть это просто та самая тема, которую я давно хочу раскрыть, потому что это очень помогло бы многим понять и узнать меня заново. даже для самых близких, для друзей, для родственников - я человек без прошлого. без целого куска прошлого, а мать это именно та часть, именно то время,  где я была утеряна. 
я писала статью о матери взапой, я строчила и строчила, убирая, перекраивая, зацензуривая, но всё равно получилось много и жёстко. 
я не спала вчера почти всю ночь подготавливая эту статью к выпуску, не спала скорее из-за нервов, чем от избытка информации.
я всю себя на изнанку вывернула, чтобы сделать это, поэтому прошу с уважением отнестись ко всему что я напишу сегодня. 
негативные комменты буду просто игнорить.

до скорой встречи.

кстати, сэм @sakmajah решила меня поддержать!! за что ей спасибо и да, она справляется лучше меня, быстрее и без всякой воды 😎

я не спала вчера почти всю ночь подготавливая эту статью к выпуску, не спала скорее из-за нервов, чем от избытка информации.
я всю себя на изнанку вывернула, чтобы сделать это, поэтому прошу с уважением отнестись ко всему что я напишу сегодня. 
негативные комменты буду просто игнорить.

до скорой встречи.

кстати, сэм @sakmajah решила меня поддержать!! за что ей спасибо и да, она справляется лучше меня, быстрее и без всякой воды 😎

text:
men’s studies: le blog des hommes et des masculinités
christoph may – fondateur de men’s studies
les témoins d’outre-mer, francetv "we all win, if men start to questioning themselves „hey, my name is christoph may. two years ago i started a blog on men and masculinity studies. i question manhood in a hypercritical way.

for example i ask for extreme masculinities in online culture wars or i write about the representation of tough guys like the men of steel, kylo ren or spiderman. what about the nerdy sexism in the big bang theory? why there is no #metoo-debate in hip-hip and rap? or why are more than 80 percent of all games in the gaming industry still running in combat-mode? questions like that. you know, it’s everywhere!

so i also wanna talk to the people, especially men. i do lectures on hatespeech and misogyny and i offer workhops for startups and business guys where you learn to kill your male privileges or how to question your male fantasies about flying to the mars, selfdriving cars or virtual reality porn.

and my experience shows, that all kind of men are really interested in that. they wanna get rid of their mansplaining-behaviour, they wanna be emotional daddies and take responsibility for their kids and best of all: they wanna support women and womens rights.

i think, a lot of men understood, that we all win, if men start to questioning themselves. so we just need to push that forward!

i wanna accallerate the crisis of men, cause i see it as a chance to give up power, to change your male view and finally to be a better man: positive, selfcritical and feminist.“ statement by #christophmay

#gender #genderstudies #feminist #feminism #männlichkeitsforschung #mensstudies #männerforschung #maleprivilege #männlichkeit #masculinity #masculinitystudies #toxicmasculinity

text:
#من_خلال_عيون_المغتصب
#احمي_نفسك . فهم بالنهاية يبحثون عن ضحية سهلة. 
#ثالثاً: دائما احملي معك سلاح تدافعين به عن نفسك كرذاذ الفلفل أو مفتاح أو صاعق كهربائي، ومن الأولى أن يكون بقبضة يدك خاصة عندما تمشين لوحدك في مكان لاتشعرين فيه بالأمان لتكوني في وضعية استعداد إذا ما قام أحد باستخدام عنصر المفاجئة لمهاجمتك.

#رابعاً: إذا قام شخص بالإمساك بك من الخلف قد لاتستطيعين التغلب عليه باستخدام القوة لكنك تسطيعين التغلب عليه باستخدام الحيلة، إذا قام بالإمساك بك حول الخصر من الخلف قومي بقرصه بشدة تحت الذراع أو مابين الكوع والإبط أو في الفخذ الداخلي العلوي، لاتستهيني بهذه الطريقة فالقرصة الشديدة تؤدي إلى اختراق الجلد وتمزيق العضلات وهي جداً مؤلمة. 
#خامساً: عندما يقوم بوضع يديه عليك، أمسكي أول اصبعين له ثم قومي بلويهما للوراء باقصى قدر ممكن وبقدر كبير من الضغط، هذه الطريقة تسبب الألم الشديد بالتالي تسبب إعاقة لحركته، بإمكانك أيضا استهداف المناطق الحساسة كالعيون والحلق والأعضاء التناسلية.

#سادساً: كوني دائما على بيّنة و دراية بما يحيط من حولك، إذا شعرت بتصرفات غريبة صادرة من شخص معين وفي منطقة مشبوهة ابتعدي أو خذي اتجاه أو طريق آخر، لاتتجاهلي هذا الشعور وثقي بغريزتك.

#سابعأ: تذكري أن الكوع هو من أقوى المفاصل في جسدك، فإذا كنت قريبة بما يكفي لاستخدامه للدفاع عن نفسك، قومي بذلك.

#ثامناً: إذا قام سارق بطلب محفظتك لاتسلميها له بيدك بل أرميها بعيداً عنك وسارعي بالهروب للإتجاه الآخر، حياتك أهم.

#تاسعاً: إذا تم القاؤكي في صندوق السيارة قومي بكسر أضواء السيارة الخلفية ثم أخرجي يدكي وقومي بالتلويح، السائق لن يراكي لكن الآخرين سيلاحظون، هذه الطريقة انقذت حياة الكثيرين. 
#عاشراً: بعض النساء لديهن عادة الركوب بسيارتهن بعد الإنتهاء من العمل أو التسوق والجلوس للقيام بإصلاح مكياجهن أو وضع قائمة أو القيام بأي نشاط آخر وهم داخل السيارة، لاتفعلي ذلك، فهناك احتمال أن شخص ما يراقبك بينما أنت جالسة في السيارة شاردة الذهن، مما يعطيه الفرصة للهجوم عليك لهذا قومي بإغلاق النوافذ وغادري حالاً خاصة إذا كنت في مكان معزول مثل المرائب تحت الارض.
يتبع.. #سارة_الفتياني
#النسوية
#metoo
#أنا_أيضا

 إذا قام شخص بالإمساك بك من الخلف قد لاتستطيعين التغلب عليه باستخدام القوة لكنك تسطيعين التغلب عليه باستخدام الحيلة، إذا قام بالإمساك بك حول الخصر من الخلف قومي بقرصه بشدة تحت الذراع أو مابين الكوع والإبط أو في الفخذ الداخلي العلوي، لاتستهيني بهذه الطريقة فالقرصة الشديدة تؤدي إلى اختراق الجلد وتمزيق العضلات وهي جداً مؤلمة. 
 عندما يقوم بوضع يديه عليك، أمسكي أول اصبعين له ثم قومي بلويهما للوراء باقصى قدر ممكن وبقدر كبير من الضغط، هذه الطريقة تسبب الألم الشديد بالتالي تسبب إعاقة لحركته، بإمكانك أيضا استهداف المناطق الحساسة كالعيون والحلق والأعضاء التناسلية.

 كوني دائما على بيّنة و دراية بما يحيط من حولك، إذا شعرت بتصرفات غريبة صادرة من شخص معين وفي منطقة مشبوهة ابتعدي أو خذي اتجاه أو طريق آخر، لاتتجاهلي هذا الشعور وثقي بغريزتك.

 تذكري أن الكوع هو من أقوى المفاصل في جسدك، فإذا كنت قريبة بما يكفي لاستخدامه للدفاع عن نفسك، قومي بذلك.

 إذا قام سارق بطلب محفظتك لاتسلميها له بيدك بل أرميها بعيداً عنك وسارعي بالهروب للإتجاه الآخر، حياتك أهم.

 إذا تم القاؤكي في صندوق السيارة قومي بكسر أضواء السيارة الخلفية ثم أخرجي يدكي وقومي بالتلويح، السائق لن يراكي لكن الآخرين سيلاحظون، هذه الطريقة انقذت حياة الكثيرين. 
 بعض النساء لديهن عادة الركوب بسيارتهن بعد الإنتهاء من العمل أو التسوق والجلوس للقيام بإصلاح مكياجهن أو وضع قائمة أو القيام بأي نشاط آخر وهم داخل السيارة، لاتفعلي ذلك، فهناك احتمال أن شخص ما يراقبك بينما أنت جالسة في السيارة شاردة الذهن، مما يعطيه الفرصة للهجوم عليك لهذا قومي بإغلاق النوافذ وغادري حالاً خاصة إذا كنت في مكان معزول مثل المرائب تحت الارض.

text:
are you a #warrior? like #wonderwoman, do you stand for justice, human rights and freedom? are you willing to fight? 
in today's world we are not being asked to physically fight... more so we are not being asked to fight at all!!! we have been trained to be sheep, go with the flow and not stir the pot.

peace and quiet is good...if it's actual peace. too many women are being oppressed, silently abused and attacked... too many men are being silence and threatened for being not-men. (whatever that means) 
it's time we stood up for something real. became our own heros. learned from our oppressive, make everyone the same and sheep mistakes. 
we are all worthy. priceless. we are all different and unique. individuals. we are all heros in our own journeys. lets make real. you are a warrior...are you ready for your quest?? #warrior #metoo #mentoo #herosjourney #masculine #feminine #worthy #priceless #beyou #authenticself #iam #soulfiresisters #angelamartinking

text:
two women eat dessert.
one curvy.
one average, according to you. 
both enjoy the delight of sweets.
meanwhile, being judged for what they eat.
the average one is seen as having a sweet tooth. 
the curvy one is deemed overweight, fat, large because of what she eats.
both are eating desserts.
both are enjoying their nights.
but one goes home satisfied.
the other, shamed. 
or is it possible both feel the same?
those looks by the waiter, by the patrons, by all eyes.
the stares.  the glares. the flares. 
those eyes.
the joy of eating gone. 
the judgment left there. 
and all for those who couldn't see themselves in you. 
blinded by the unseen truth. 
dessert is dessert.
sugar is sugar.
food is food.
enjoy. -the unseen truth of judgment 
#bodyshamingneedstostop #positivebodyimage #bbw #curvy #curvygirl #womenempower #socialjustice #loveoffood #dessert #loveyourself #smilebackathaters
#standfirm #poems #poetry #girlpower #metoo @poemsporn_ @poets @poetryfoundation @poetsorg @poetry.cosmos #thecultivatedfool

tied up published in @ferocemagazine ⚡️.
•
'tied up' is a statement about humanity, our diversity and many ranges of our emotions. 
one of the qualities that make us sentient is the society we have built and the web of relationships we are a part of. we try to find balance in ourselves and in our relationships. 
moments of bliss, clarity and togetherness punctuated by moments of struggle and confusion, we are all essentially tied up together.
.

text: this is a much needed post 🙌🏽👸🏽 ———————————————————————————— as a man it’s very important to educate yourself on how to treat a woman. when a female rejects you, breaks up with you or simply chooses to be who she wants to be! you have absolutely no right to go & spread rumors about her. to disrespect her or defame her. to harass or threaten her. when a female tells you no when you’re coming off too hard, or when she says no to a sexual act! it simply means no & she has every right to do so. when a female dresses in shorts, dresses or a revealing outfit it gives no one the right to slut shame her, touch her or force themself on her because she was “asking for it!” these deranged individuals who look at women in such a way should be treated the same & punished. there’s something wrong with them not the woman! i have had to deal with so many of these kind of individuals & incidents. i was sexually harassed as a child & as an adult by people my parents trusted & some i trusted smh. experiencing all of this didn’t make me weak, instead it made me stronger & gave me the fuel i needed to be able to speak for other women. it didn’t make me feel bad about myself, it just showed me how deranged these individuals were. ———————————————————————————— let women be women & little girls be little girls without placing your judgements & rules on them 🌸🌸 being able to speak up about traumatic issues takes courage. do not slut shame us, abuse us or silence our voices. instead stand with us. speak up for us & treat us like you would your mother or daughter 💋♥️ #projectvhouston #thepowerofv #timesup #livelovehealinspire #notinmyname #metoo #humantraffickingawareness #forwomenbywomen #educateyourself #womenempowerment #womeninspiringwomen #bloggerlife

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

read this👇👇
_

casual harassment and staring has made me so conscious and uncomfortable that i think 10 times before going alone somewhere 😕
_
.
.
.
.

'tied up' is a statement about humanity, our diversity and many ranges of our emotions. 
one of the qualities that make us sentient is the society we have built and the web of relationships we are a part of. we try to find balance in ourselves and in our relationships. 
moments of bliss, clarity and togetherness punctuated by moments of struggle and confusion, we are all essentially tied up together.

text:
“ho capito solo da 10 anni che ‘no’ è una frase completa.” - jane fonda
• solo uno dei tanti doni che mi sta facendo questo documentario su @netflixit: “feminists: what were they thinking”, scoperto grazie a andrea di @tlon.it . e con l’occasione riporto quanto scritto da lui:
“in quanto uomo ho bisogno di un controllo mensile dei livelli di femminismo nel sangue. [...] non perché io sia cattivo e smemorato, ma perché dopo un po’ negli uomini parte il programma automatico ‘ma in fondo i problemi non son così gravi, non esageriamo, c’è di peggio’. così ho imparato a impostare una sorta di sveglia interiore che mi proponga ogni tot del materiale utile a ricordarmi quanto sia vasto il divario tra uomini e donne, quanto sia stato fatto in termini di libertà e parità, quanto rischiamo di perdere in questa fase cruciale e quanto ancora c’è da fare.” • #feminist #feminists #feminism #femminismo #metoo #janefonda #documentary #netflix #netflixitalia #documentario #motivation #motivational #motivationalquotes #qotd #quote #quotes #noisno #consent #womenpower #thisisnotconsent

text:
-
교육계 재립 촉구 시위에 다녀온 소감문 입니다.
연대하겠습니다.
.
‘청소년 자매들의 용기와 절규가 묻히지 않도록 항상 연대하겠습니다. 용기내주셔서 감사합니다. 더 크게 목소리 내겠습니다.’ 라는 내용으로 스쿨미투 손글씨 운동에 참여한적이 있다. 목소리를 낼 기회가 없었다는 핑계에 잠시 잊었던 나를 반성했던 자리였다. 또한 오늘 이 자리를 통해 희망찬 앞날이 보였다.
🥊우진김옷없어서튀김옷입음
.
내가 청소년이었을때 인지하지 못해서, 예민하단 소리가 듣기 싫어서, 용기를 내지 못해서 그냥 지나쳤던 불합리한 것들에대해 지금의 청소년 자매들은 문제제기를 하고 잘못된 것들을 바로잡으려 용감하게 노력하고 있다. 그들의 용기에 박수를 보내며 나 역시 내 자리에서 할 수있는 일들을 하고 함께 연대할것이다. 잘못된것을 바로잡으려하는 노력은 절대 예민한것이 아니며 그 노력을 예민함으로 치부하고 묻어버리려는 사람들이 잘못된것이다. 우리는 이 확신을 가지고 더 나아갈 것이다.
🥊버자이나 울프
.
불편한걸 불편하다고 하지 못했던, 못하게 했던 학창시절의 분위기는 지금도 잊을 수가 없다. 그러나 지금은 그 부조리함들을  밖으로 나와 같이 고발하고 저항하는 자리에 함께 할 수 있다는 것 만으로도 뿌듯하다. 아직 갈 길은 멀지만 더욱 보호 받아야할 미성년자들의 권리가 보장되었으면 한다.
🥊갓골무
.
과거에 나는 침묵하고 가만히 있었는데 현재 학생들은 분노하고 소리내고 있다. 예전에 말하지 못했던 나의 몫만큼 용기내고 소리치며 청소년 자매들과 연대할 것이다. 어서 교육계는 가해교사들을 처벌하라. 🥊아이스커피
.

text:
gun control. a topic that is widely debated worldwide, especially in america -  a topic that gets brought up time and time again with little to no amendments being made, despite thousands being killed every year. in the uk we have had less than 50 massacres or mass killings since 61 ad - 28 of them done either with firearms or bombs. 
in contrast to this, the thousand oak mass shooting was the 307th mass shooting in america this year, with over 12000  victims losing their lives to firearms. the deaths of the 12000 americans this year impact not only the lives of the victims but also the lives of the families - 12000 human beings dead, likely many more than 100,000 humans effected terribly and irreversibly. 
all for what ? the president of the united states of america, donald trump, amongst many other leading politicians, accepts an absolutely colossal sum of money each year (some may call it bribery) from some of the biggest gun companies in the usa, mainly the national rifle association. this has to stop, it is so, so absurd that someone who has been accused  of sexual harassment, someone who wants to erase the rights of a group of people just because of their gender orientation and someone who cares more about money than the welfare of 'his' people is allowed to be the president . unfortunately, it is not something we can immediately change but trump making crude jokes about the deaths of people and giving those affected 'his prayers' is not enough . praying, despite it sometimes helping  the individual mentally, will not stop the shootings, nor will it bring those who have been brutally killed back . america, we beg you, please introduce gun control now, before yet more innocent people die . imagine if it was your kid that was killed whilst in school, an everyday thing where the biggest threat should be detention, because someone with a gun had killed them. would you want to change gun laws then, to stop other people's kids and families from being torn apart, or would you sit back, lap up the money you're being paid and say that it's ok because 'people have a right to bear arms' ? cont in comments .

text:
sessions live 2018 recap: yesterday i had the privilege to attend this amazing event created by @estherperelofficial |  a day long conference focused on issues of masculinity and how we as professionals (and non-professionals) can help men specifically and better inform our work | 
it was the most energized and excited i’ve felt about working with men since moving to new york in january of this year. working as a therapist is often lonely and isolating, especially in a new city with few connections. working as a therapist whose primary focus and goal is to help men can also be isolating, because many people do not want to “take on the challenge” of helping men or know how to connect with them |
sitting in that conference room yesterday with hundreds live and thousands streaming across the world i felt more connected, inspired, motivated and aligned with the work i want to do than ever |
men need us. men want to have these conversations about intimacy, connection, relationships, sex, erotic pleasure; but not enough people are willing to listen and offer guidance. this is the masculinity paradox. we (as women and a society) can’t tell men we want and expect more from them and then not offer a solution or turn away when they ask for help. we must all step up and help each other |

text:
every day. every day for nearly a year i have relived odella’s birth. with that, i have inadvertently relived and remember leigh’s and joy’s births. and i have grieved. grieved for my first birth that could have been so much better if i had been respected and listened to. 
i did not suddenly hand over my autonomy when i got pregnant. 
i did not consent to: episiotomy, repeated cervical checks, or pitocin. i did not consent to being treated like a paycheck. i too was bullied, coerced, and talked down to. when i timidly voiced my opposition i was bulldozed. and really, this barely scratches the surface. 
tell me this. if an angry man has a hand in your vagina, and you’re crying because he’s hurting you and you don’t want this...what would you call that??? when the nurses don’t want to “make him upset” even at the expense of your fundamental right to refuse a non-emergent and completely unnecessary medical procedure that will alter the course of your entire labor, that’s a clue.

and let me just say i did not know this wasn’t normal. 
my homebirths have been so healing, but they don’t make up for my first experience. i loved them, but a woman should not have to choose homebirth because she’s scared of a hospital and obstetricians. you have the right to be supported in the birth you want and in the location you want. 
so a big old f you to the doctor who said i should “consider having this baby abdominally” just because i cried during a forced cervical check. to the doctor who did not speak to me as a fully functional autonomous being but instead turned to the nurse “let’s get this girl an epidural. we all know how she handles pain”. and to the impatient doctor who cut my perineum without my consent while muttering to himself “didn’t want to do that”. “bull. shit.” says the same perineum who birthed two more babies, one 2 full pounds heavier, without a single tear.

and then, at the end of it all. with my newborn squalling across the room, he had the absolute gall to say “hey, i could be home for dinner right now” when i asked if he was done with my stitches so i could hold the new human that just came from my body.

so...yes. fuck you. #obstetricalviolence

tempo, vai devagar...

text:
women working full time in the united states are paid 80% of what men are paid and are not expected to reach pay equity with men until 2119 and 13% of american women ages 18-64 are living below the federal poverty level, compared with 10% of men.  for ages 65 and older 11% of women and 8% of men were living in poverty.

this is bad for growth, for reducing poverty and for social cohesion.  eliminating the gender pay gap by increasing women's levels of pay to those of men could cut the poverty rate for working women in half.

text:
the architecture lobby took action to create a solidarity network to end the silence and complicity that enables structural, systemic conditions of abuse within workplaces and academia. the network has evolved into the solidarity bloc: an informal, non-institutional group meant for community support and discussion. the term ‘bloc’ relates to the space of a community, in ways that can be abstract as well as physical.
-
you can help by taking a stand to support people who have experienced sexual harassment in the field of architecture. join the solidarity bloc by filling out the first form :
http://architecture-lobby.org/project/metoo-solidarity-bloc/#join
-
if you are experiencing sexual harassment at your workplace and seek support, please fill out the second form. we will connect you with a member of the solidarity bloc who can help. lean on the solidarity bloc.
-
the solidarity bloc is organized by the architecture lobby’s  #metoo / #endpatriarchitecture working group (@acetaminophen). by joining the bloc, you will be publicly identified as a supporter. the names and stories of those who seek support will remain confidential; we will not publicize details without your express permission.

text:
it’s been a little quiet over here this week. my full attention has been on my project - which has absolutely zero to do with food and 100% everything to do with women power. .
.
you guys might know that i was assaulted when living in istanbul. to be clear - this can (and does) happen everywhere. it just so happened that my story is here. the thing that stuck with me most is how i was treated by the men at the police station like it was my fault when trying to report. i left with the feeling that i wasn’t worth anything as a foreign female. it’s not ok that these things still happen all over the world. it’s not ok that women are being systematically silenced. it’s not ok that women do the same work but earn less. it’s not ok that men are making laws and decisions impacting women - like regulations around sanitary products. and the list goes on and on. we have all experienced the inequality. have been groped, cat called, overlooked for promotions as being in the age of having children, minimised to our looks rather than our brains.
.
there’s so much that needs to be said. there are so many stories that need to be heard. so many voices that want to be raised. .
.
so that’s what my new project will evolve around. i’m not quite ready to share it here, yet, but watch this space 👀💪🏼
.
.
much love to you guys. women and men. 😘
.
.

text:
omg i changed my mind. like i said grow, regroup and grow some more. this was my first mind anyway. i was tryimg to be nice according to the worlds standards and thats not me.

the noise is waaay to much for my sensitive brain and spirit. all of it. again nobody is perfect so even the best of intentions grieve my spirit sometimes. i am not going to be exclusive or selective. humans will be human.

after the flood of private messages and some totally inappropriate and inconsiderate i as an individual am disappearing from #socialmedia. i dont much like it anyway. i'm an autistic introvert and when i engage with you one on one i'm going out of my way even if you dont appreciate or realize it.

if you love me dont worry. this is #selfcare and #stewardship. if ive been mentoring you, i will continue at the scheduled times only. all i have to give is wisdom and love. if you don't value that then by all means unfollow. i am a friend to many. but really have very very few true friends. which will really be revealed right now.

no more private messages or offline conversations with the @sugarfreecoach my number is inactive unless you have been screened.

if you have something to say and can't say it publicly than you shouldn't be saying it. that goes for questions, advice, and etc.

🇫🇷 hello,
et une nouvelle interview pour le recueil #desauteursautoeditessemobilisentcontreleharcelementderue 😉
tout se passe sur la page facebook du même nom (ou en cherchant @recueilharcelementderue).
le recueil est aussi répertorié sur goodreads et booknode pour l’instant 😊
en tout, 17 nouvelles et donc 17 voix pour s’exprimer sur le harcèlement dans les lieux publics envers des femmes, des couples homosexuels, des victimes du racisme, etc.
des genres et des tons différents.
la version 📚 fait 350 pages 😊
bonne aprem 🍁
•••
📒 vous pouvez retrouver mes livres, les ajouter à votre pal et consulter des extraits sur les sites de lecture comme babelio, livraddict, booknode et goodreads à mon nom d’autrice s. n. lemoing 😊
🛍 ils sont disponibles gratuitement en emprunt avec amazon kindle ou à 2.99€ pour les romans et 0.99€ pour les épisodes de lescalicesdutemps au format ebook, et entre 8 et 11€ pour les versions papier 📖
•••
🇬🇧 hi,
another really interesting introduction with this interview of the 11th author of the street harassment anthology 😊
each author explain why they wrote it & if it’s a personal story.
there’s a facebook page for the book. 17 novellas have been selected, 17 voices for women, queer people, people of color, etc. who have been harassed.
have a great time 🍁

link in bio.

.
the resurrection...of power. .
if you are a “respectable” person you don’t speak her name often. her identity and reputation thrown in amongst the trash used for derogatory purposes or when a man wants to boast about how much he’s gotten lately. many women and men would like to keep her in the shadows, with all the other delinquents, where she belongs. .
those of us who remember her power, knew it was only a matter of time and that she’d come when she was ready. to the #lovewarriors who came before us and those who still stand with her, thank you for playing a long game. players for this team require diligence, a certain level of safety and a realization that #timesup. of course she rose through the shadow. it’s her way, bringing herself forward to reunite with the light. it was in the recognition of her #love, that many people gained the courage to come forward and tell their stories #metoo. .
.
a resurrection of this nature takes a certain kind of resiliency, commitment and aptitude. the grabbing ways of men who believe the lies of her inadequacies have been the exact recipe to bring forth her bitter sweet subtle power. .
.
depth eludes those who play a surface level game. the mysteries of her unknown to those who refuse to honor their birthplace. access requires surrender, receptivity, care, attention and compassion.  the minute you put a timeline or set an agenda she will close up and you will be denied access. she’s not interested in results as much as she is interested in connection. connection allows for opening, fluidity and release into feeling. rewiring the web of our nervous system after each and every storm...she creates through presence. the patriarchy thought she could be shamed into subordination. little did they know that her liberation would be found underground in the dungeon where she was sent to die. .
for it’s in this resurrection that we now can see her beautiful seed blooming. .
11:11:11
.

text:
as i’m feeling scared about what is next for me, i decided to write my feelings rather than bottle it up and feel ashamed about feeling afraid - it’s hard to take courage in this world, i find it really hard to share parts of myself and my creative work 😰 - as someone who controls fear by hiding away it takes a lot to build up the courage to be seen and heard - i get overwhelmed easily but i’m learning that’s ok as long as i know myself and continue to get to know who i am, then i can learn to accept this and put boundaries in place for myself. 
although i find it hard, i have to make courage a practice for myself which means doing something i’m afraid of every day or at a pace that is best for me. every day i want to hide away but my inner feeling keeps pushing me to show up. saying to myself that i am enough, and to keep being kind to myself while remembering that it’s all about the process is crucial for me 🧡 #courage #selflove #selfkindness #fear #afraid #comfort #comfortzone #choosecourage #itsok #itsoktonotbeok #yourenotalone #metoo #feelings #thoughts #challenge #anxietywarrior  #trusttheprocess #process  #creativeprocess #chooselove #wellbeing #knowyourself #boundaries #perfectionism #overwhelmed #scared #anxiety #youareenough #vulnerable #imperfect

text:
i am here. i will listen.  if you need an ear, reach out to me and i will be present for you.  in the last few days a lot of truths have been revealed and i am so grateful to the women who have come out and shared their story. @cerclecheung @gigisplendid @marlofisken @irmingardmayer @sistertothesun, i know that was not easy. i am in awe of your bravery and strength. thank you for exposing this predator and protecting women. this behavior, these attacks are unacceptable and because of you there will be a high probability that this cycle will end. and to the women who have not come forward, i understand. your privacy is your right. and i believe you too. •
with that i say: do not hire @cbtrn. this man took advantage of, coerced, and sexually assaulted numerous women who were just trying to make beautiful art. i am disgusted with cristian buitron. i taught at body & pole for many years and saw him frequently at studio events. he was a bit of an odd duck but i ignored it since he was working for the studio. we were friendly. i feel lucky never to have been solo with him. but, motherfucker, does it make me angry now knowing that i was in the presence of a monster who was preying on my friends, colleagues and students.  i am hopeful that through sharing this information that he will be exterminated from our sacred space. and that the other circles he was in: fashion, ju jitsu, model photography have read these stories to protect themselves as well. •
the upside of this is i believe that now more women are allowing themselves forgiveness, expecting respect and not allowing themselves to be run over.  not by this man or any other person that preys on us.  we have collectively grown stronger. and i am grateful for that. 
#believewomen #metoo #ibelieveyou

text:
you should never have to apologize for being you and you shouldn't need to change yourself either.

anyone who insists that you should become a certain way (especially if that certain way makes you uncomfortable) simply doesn't deserve you. simply let them go. 
i know it's easier said than done, but once you realise your true value, it should be much easier.

you deserve to be surrounded by people who appreciate you. flaws, quirks and all. people who never make you doubt yourself or doubt how great you are. people who make you feel all the more confident in yourself.

if you ever do change, it should be of your own accord, not because someone pressured you into it.

you're special in your own right and you should only strive to be the best you that you can be. no one else can do you like you can, so freaking own it and never look back.

i myself struggle with being unapologetic about being myself, but with time it should get better.

text: like most families in today’s world mine is no different and full of dysfunction. the hard part about seeing truth is....seeing truth. they aren’t different, but i am. i’m choosing to acknowledge the huge elephant in the room, while being kind and loving, knowing full well the mess that is going on around me. my hope isn’t in my family it’s in god my father who will never let me down. he continues to be my hope, helps me remain in gratitude and most of all teaches me about love for myself and for those who continue to harm me. that’s freedom even if the truth hurts. #family #freedom #dysfunctional #hope #grateful #freedom #truth #love #loveyourself #loveyourneighbor #metoo #414ministry

text:
i get to give talks all over the country on issues of race and gender justice, womxn’s freedom, violence, aapi womxn’s issues, school discipline and imprisonment, the power of research, and education. i’ve spoken in front of senators, congresswomen, in front of thousands and on television. been at this for more than 20 years. best part of this struggle called life? was having our mom come to be a part of this work and at the first historical conference re: asian and pacific islander women and girl leadership, #imready2018, @aapiwomenlead. my mom called the next day, sent photos and said she was so proud and so happy to be there. she said, someone gave me a flower. my mom, dear ones, came straight from dialysis - got dressed up - to join us. she said, “i’m so proud.” she is a vietnamese war refugee and survivor. my sis and i did this for her. gratitude for this life, for all survivors, for the many who came and told their stories, for those who held space, and for every single one of us - every damn day. we are out here living the hell out of life, even when + because they try to take our freedoms away. never let anyone else, especially this place, define your value or worth. ever. #fightingforfreedom all day. #playbig (more photos and thank yous to come 📸:@techboogie) .
.
.
#intersectionalfeminism #metoo #womenofcolor #aapi #peopleofcolor #metoomovement #timesup

text:
"social media platforms have become integral in shaping social and political narratives. these platforms have given many people a voice - a voice that they weren’t sure they had in today's society." the advent of social media was a very significant change that happened at the turn of the millennium. its popularity has grown tremendously from the time the first social media site, six degrees, was created in 1997. today it brings together people from all over the world. however, it has done more than just provide a platform to connect with people and share content, it's now a place where every person can voice their opinion and speak out on poltical and social issues. and thus, the age of digital activism was born. 
social media has played a huge role in making the public aware of many issues that exist in the world today. it has become a very effective platform to rally people together for a cause. there used to be a time when leaders had to go talk to people on the streets and in their houses to get them to follow a cause. now they seem to do the same by sending out a tweet. social media platforms have become integral in shaping social and political narratives. yes, there are dark sides to this but these platforms have also given many people a voice - a voice that they weren’t sure they had in today's society. even though #metoo received a lot of backlash it helped many people realize that they aren't alone.

digital activism allows people to show that they care about world issues. it helps us voice our opinions in a public forum. however talking can only do so much, change requires action. social media is a good place to start a social movement, but to sustain such a movement we must work in the real world not a virtual one. 
#ted #tedx #millennium

text_retweet:
let’s get it. . . . *repost @seewun with @get_repost
・・・
i get to give talks all over the country on issues of race and gender justice, womxn’s freedom, violence, aapi womxn’s issues, school discipline and imprisonment, the power of research, and education. i’ve spoken in front of senators, congresswomen, in front of thousands and on television. been at this for more than 20 years. best part of this struggle called life? was having our mom come to be a part of this work and at the first historical conference re: asian and pacific islander women and girl leadership, feminism, issues, #imready2018, @aapiwomenlead. my mom called the next day, sent photos and said she was so proud and so happy to be there. she said, someone gave me a flower. my mom, dear ones, came straight from dialysis - got dressed up - to join us. she said, “i’m so proud.” she is a vietnamese war refugee and survivor. my sis and i did this for her. gratitude for this life, for all survivors, for those who came and told their stories, for those who held space, and for every single one of us - every damn day. we are out here living the hell out of life, even when they try to take our freedoms away. never let anyone else, especially this place, define your value or worth. ever. #fightingforfreedom all day. #playbig (more photos and thank yous to come 📸:@techboogie) .
.
.
#intersectionalfeminism #metoo #womenofcolor #aapi #peopleofcolor #metoomovement #timesup

text:
sexual assault and harassment is not only prevalent in the climbing community, it is overwhelmingly frequent. 
in a survey administered by #safeoutside, 1 in 3 participants reported to have experienced some form of sexual assault or harassment. of the women who answered, almost half (47.3%) indicated that they were a victim of some form of sexual misconduct. “after experiencing sexual harassment and assault, 45.4 percent of respondents—and 54.5 percent of women—said the incident changed the way they climb.” this is unacceptable. 
i have my own experience with this in the climbing community. sexual misconduct ranges from catcalling, inappropriate messages, to physical advances. i am not speaking only to those who commit these acts, also to victims, bystanders, and those who are simply unaware. educate yourselves, protect yourselves, and help those in your community do the same.

we must do better together. link to the full article in my bio. #metoo

text:
first, there is no one method or formula for determining reparations. #poland #fascism #justice. 
so much of the violence we experience is personalized. violence is always shared by other people and communities, yet how it affects us is embodied and related to who we are in this earth walk. that's why this method was designed for people like you and #metoo.

second, calculating reparations is always an economic and spiritual practice.

above all, the spiritual dimension of this method is central, and #survivors must lead each initiative. the point is to foster #healing, not pay for therapy and legal costs, and give people the support we require to #create solutions for ourselves and our beloved communities. so, what does healing mean for you as a survivor of the violence you seek to stop? given your daily life and needs at this time, what do you need to put in place to learn and apply the method?

from a purely economic #perspective, what aspects of healing can financial reparations facilitate? this question is the most direct, but it isn't as simple as it sounds. for example, you might desire therapy and know that therapists cost a rate of, say $60-250 an hour in your town. what if no therapist in your local #belovedcommunity speaks your mother language of #quechua or #polish and that's the language in which you #sense the world? what is the honest price tag for your therapy sessions if you have to travel three hours to see a therapist who shares your cultural, linguistic, #ancestral perspective?

what else is at #play when it comes to #money? emotions such as grief and #anger, fear and pain, shame and guilt always #bubble to the surface when delving into traumatic experiences, and poverty is its own #trauma. what can make this #learning process a means of healing financial trauma in your personal life and that of your beloved community?

calculating for #reparations is traveling through time and body. it means seeing a #horror happen again and again and again from multiple perspectives like the child who misses his father and the mother and six aunties #grieving their daughter in a nation, language, and culture that doesn't feel like home – and isn't. #home.

text: gene tierney as miranda wells in dragonwyck (1946) | martin scorsese called gene tierney one of the most underrated actresses of hollywood’s golden era. her name is indeed not quite as well-remembered as those of contemporaries such as grace kelly, who replaced her in mogambo. tierney has been very open about struggles she has faced both in her career and personal life, specifically her mental health issues. at some point she also recalled an encounter with director ernst lubitsch, who continuously shouted at her during the shooting of heaven can wait. in a proto-#metoo-era move she requested not to be shouted at again, showing that she was unafraid to stand up for herself. it worked. after her intervention, lubitsch and herself went along famously well.

but i didn't ask for 
the scars that remain
printed blue
you try to stitch my

but i comfort it 
everyday

text:
it's sunday, and we're gonna get real. see this character? i used to hate harley quinn. i hated how stupid she was for staying with joker, and then something happened. 
i left an abusive relationship. i thought it would never happen to me, i thought i was too smart, and while i was in it? i threw on a smile and excused everything he did. i had no idea i was doing it, until after i got out. none. and i finally understood that no matter how smart you are, it can happen to you. 
i hope after that i've learned to be more sympathetic and less judgemental. i never understood, how can you not realize it when it's happening? i still don't understand tbh. but i know it's true. 
i'm greatful to the friends and family that pulled me back up onto my feet after it. harley turned to anger. funny enough, despite my usual red lantern standing: i didn't. see, the battle after i left wasn't with him. it was with myself. it took time to crawl out of the suicidal pit i'd been set down into when i trusted him with my life. it took time to stop blaming myself for his choices. took time to realize the mutual "friends" i held on to out of fear and desperation to have something familiar remain, they were a fitsful of rattlesnakes. see, i wasn't mad at him. i was mad at myself, for not seeing it and leaving him sooner. for not seeing how many toxic people he had set up around me, and leaving them sooner. 
silver lining: i'm wiser. stronger. i know now who i can truly depend on, and am quicker to take out the trash. 
back to harley. i don't hate her anymore. i hate the joker. and the culture surrounding them. 
see i don't fight abusers. i fight the society that gives them places to operate freely in. if zero tolerance for violence, including those who excuse and condone violence, makes me "unreasonable"? good. 
the only way you'll ever see me cosplay harley, is in activism against domestic violence. putting the shame where it belongs, and the strength in the hands of those rebuilding their lives. you will overcome this. 
#harleyquinn #domesticviolence #realtalk #metoo #zerotolerance #domesticviolenceawareness #survivingabuse #superhero

text:
under veckan besökte jag och @akcnfoto tre gymnasieskolor för att prata med ungdomar om #metoo. för ett år sedan vittnade tiotusentals människor från samhällets alla skikt om de utbredda problemen med sexism, trakasserier och övergrepp. har något ändrats sedan dess? och hur upplever dagens ungdomar tiden efter metoo? i artikeln finns svar från alla som medverkade i enkäten, här kommer tre av dem (från vänster till höger i bilden):
▪️
michelle hruska, 18:
▫️
”den mest konkreta förändringen är samtyckeslagen. jag märker att många fler killar förstår vad samtycke är. däremot vet jag inte om det är för att de förstår att samtycke är viktigt eller för att de är rädda för att ’åka dit’. det är inte lika tabubelagt för en kille att vara feminist nu, förut var de mycket mer macho. men machostrukturerna finns självklart kvar fortfarande. jag hörde senast förra veckan att det var skämt om våldtäkter, att de inte ville ha en dotter för att de ’bara blir våldtagna iallafall’.”
▪️
lisa ahlén, 18:
▫️
”killarna uppmärksammas, de som tycker att de inte får göra saker på samma sätt längre. de säger att de inte kan eller får ragga på tjejer längre. om jag vet hur man kan prata med någon utan att exempelvis tafsa tror jag inte det är så svårt att låta bli. jag blir besviken när man inte fokuserar på att förändra sånt här. jag tror mycket handlar om grundläggande värderingar och uppfostran. nu har det kommit en samtyckeslag, men normerna måste också förändras.”
▪️
harry håkansson, 18:
▫️
”vi killar vågar snacka om det mer med varandra, vad som är och inte är okej. jag tror väldigt få killar pratade om sånt innan metoo men efteråt har det varit mycket mer öppet. jag har tidigare tänkt att vissa män inte är kapabla till att göra något av det som har rapporterats om i medier, men nu har förvåningen försvunnit. nu har snacket svalnat av lite och det är synd. det är viktigt att snacka om sånt här hela tiden när vissa har svårt att förstå var gränser går.”
name: Atilla Yoldas

text: “i would rather be a rebel than a slave “ e pankhurst ... maybe for us lucky ones feminism feels a little done but that is not the case for the majority, all over the world women and children are still the poorest citizens -fewer rights and more abused- as an example when i spend a year teaching in a remote part of nepal they only ate meat once a week, a chicken in a pot on sunday’s and always the men ate first, then the children, then the women. this is only a mild example but that is common place so we have to keep fighting until every women has equally and opportunity !!!! #equalrights #metoomovement #metoo #feminist #feminism

text:
*trigger warning*
on this date, 7 years ago, i was raped. i was thirteen years old. he was a senior, played varsity soccer, and very popular. he told me no one would believe me, everyone would just think i had an obsessive crush. i believed him. i stayed silent and hated myself for what happened. no words can ever explain the pain or horror i felt that night. i felt dirty. no matter how many showers i took, i couldn’t wash away the shame i felt. it took control of my life. over a year later, i began therapy, finally told someone what happened, and started to heal. every night during this time, i would read “still i rise” by maya angelou. i am forever grateful for the strength these words brought me. i broke my silence and reported the assault. i will never again be silenced or victimized. i have found healthy ways to channel my pain and rage from my experiences. through an amazing non-profit called peace over violence, i became a state-certified violence prevention specialist. now, i teach classes throughout lausd to middle schoolers and high schoolers on sexual assault/harassment, domestic violence, healthy relationships, etc. my trauma does not define who i am but i sure as hell am a stronger and more compassionate person because of it. 
silence perpetuates violence. if we want change, we need to speak up. we cannot keep living in a society that stands by and tolerates this behavior. 
consent is not passive, it is affirmative! your body is your own. you are entitled to free will, don’t let anyone take that from you. to my fellow survivors: i believe you and i am here for you. #metoo

text:
this is me. i don't want to share my whole face because i want to keep it anonymous. at the moment no one knows about this account here.
it's so hard for me at the moment. my mental health is quite bad and i have just no one to talk to. i have one friend here in germany and my other friends (who are also my best friends and the only ones who know about my past and everything) are living in different countries. i so wish i could see them more often, they're the only ones i can talk to without watching what to say. it's crazy because i just know them for 1,5 years now and they're the best people in my life. 
i had a mental breakdown last week because they had a group video call without me and told me they couldn't reach me. but of course my anxiety was like 'they didn't try to reach you, they wanted to make this call without you because no one likes you'. it's crazy how anxiety and trust issues work right? i know they would never hurt me on purpose and my mind just tells me otherwise. i fucking hate it.
i'm crying right now because i miss them so much and i don't know when i can see them again. ☹

text:
kicking off @vital_apparel  we never knew what the outcome would be. all we knew was there was a problem in this world and we wanted to be part of the solution.
-
we took a negative situation and turned it into something positive. mental health is a growing issue world wide and its currently not getting the attention it deserves.
-
1/5 adults in the u.s currently struggle with mental illnesses.
-
1/5 youth experiences severe mental health illnesses during their lifetime.
-
suicide is currently the second leading cause of death in the united states. -
we feel there are still many gray areas in mental health research therefore each month we’re happy that we’re able to donate to @bbrfoundation to further mental health research.
-
most importantly our journey and mission would not be possible without each and everyone of you!
-
it’s amazing to see everyone rep our gear, share our post, and spread awareness about mental health!
-
blessed to have formed such a strong mental health community that share our vision! -
let’s break the stigma together!
-

text:
🗣 digital activism panel is on nov. 17 @ 12pm. in the wake of the #metoo movement, locally-based filmmakers and artists explore the implications this may have for women and trans folks belonging to communities of colour, black communities, and indigenous communities locally, and beyond.

meet our panelist shazia javed, a york mfa film alumni and award-winning filmmaker. her documentary film namrata was produced by the national film board of canada and was a finalist for three ampia awards. shazia’s work has screened at prestigious film festivals including hot docs, doxa, global visions, and durban international film festival. 
support #rpff18 and join the discussion. link to more details in our bio!

kicking off @vital_apparel  we never knew what the outcome would be. all we knew was there was a problem in this world and we wanted to be part of the solution.
-
we took a negative situation and turned it into something positive. mental health is a growing issue world wide and its currently not getting the attention it deserves.
-
1/5 adults in the u.s currently struggle with mental illnesses.
-
1/5 youth experiences severe mental health illnesses during their lifetime.
-
suicide is currently the second leading cause of death in the united states. -
we feel there are still many gray areas in mental health research therefore each month we’re happy that we’re able to donate to @bbrfoundation to further mental health research.
-
most importantly our journey and mission would not be possible without each and everyone of you!
-
it’s amazing to see everyone rep our gear, share our post, and spread awareness about mental health!
-
blessed to have formed such a strong mental health community that share our vision! -
let’s break the stigma together!

text:
a 6 day challenge, beginning today 11/11 from wherever you are in the world, in ig to fb, no limits. this is in honor of #metoo....rising from our own ashes to claim your space on your terms, if there were no objectification or fear of violation...how do you feel attractive, sexy and sensual embodying yourself? what if we could create a new norm of safety to express in puritanical america? selfies, step on up! allow me to offer some of my own soul-utions by assisting you with self inquiring prompts, replacing fear and trauma in our hearts & psych with #onlythankyou #iloveyou #withartandsoul

it is so interesting, i feel very passionate about this movement for too many reasons to detail, yet i felt great shame and resistance when thinking of taking action and inviting women (et al) to take this leap, afraid that noone will want to dance, because...afraid of judgement and knowing the self judgement will stop women. i figure if i feel this much reservation, i got to put it out. upgrades and input in language on this welcome. #nakedwerise is facing and sharing our truth, showing our vulnerability and being willing to show ourselves unapologetically and provocatively, since we are still sexual and sensual beings filled with radiance no matter what experiences we have had in the past, they are not a reflection of our worthiness to shine our light and beauty. 
i welcome you to try this for your self.  empower yourself by investing this time in yourself with art and soul, investing the time to reflect and command your own beliefs and amplify your truth.  #truenature #changingyourmindinyourbody

invitation: 
1. there will be a prompt every day for reflection, but really there are no rules only innovation 
2. share a selfie or an image that represents how you desire to feel or strive to feel like

3. feel the fear and do it anyway, this is about taking a stand for yourself

4. if you wish, share a story or what you are calling forth in yourself & the world

5. share with your friends you love to upgrade together and witness + support each other: #nakedwerise #truenature 
benefits: 
feeling validated, embodied, inspired and more self acceptance = amazing ❤🙏😁🌈

text:
i yelled “me too”.
the world went quiet and f*ck it felt so good to see you move.
to find your eyes in mine and say “oh baby girl”,
to cry and you cried too.
i need that,
i need to see that somewhere love breathes hope for me and you,
for all the faces turned to mine,
to find your hand reach mine and tears that made me blind,
entitled in the witnessing of others,
you found a way to stretch to all the brothers,
all our sisters that felt week,
all the words they cannot speak for fear of being found.
you sang the words, i cried,
so did the crowd.
you let your vulnerability shine rayes,
and mimicked in the mooring of the waves,
you start a ripple, still in early days
but now i am more proud of you,
for making space for me to shout “me too”.
#metoo #metoomovement #raye #shine #speak #voice #speakyourtruth #nomoreshame #nomoresilence #nomoreshadows #averyfuckingbravestrongwoman #verystrongwoman #nowthisher  #thekla #bristol #liberty @raye you have shifted something in me. thank you for taking the time to speak with me, thank you for sharing your message and making people feel less alone. thank you. #thankyou #freedom
name: Liberty Tate Walker
tweet_full:
i yelled “me too”.
the world went quiet and f*ck it felt so good to see you move.
to find your eyes in mine and say “oh baby girl”,
to cry and you cried too.
i need that,
i need to see that somewhere love breathes hope for me and you,
for all the faces turned to mine,
to find your hand reach mine and tears that made me blind,
entitled in the witnessing of others,
you found a way to stretch to all the brothers,
all our sisters that felt week,
all the words they cannot speak for fear of being found.
you sang the words, i cried,
so did the crowd.
you let your vulnerability shine rayes,
and mimicked in the mooring of the waves,
you start a ripple, still in early days
but now i am more proud of you,
for making space for me to shout “me too”.

text:
sometimes i think about dying. not about suicide, but really about dying. dying by a really bad and sadic way. be sure to really hurt for my last 30 secondes alive. when people ask me why i tell them it’s because i’m ashamed. i’m ashamed of the choice i make. of the decision i take. of the heart i broke. of the heart i loved. of the boys i kissed. of the world where i lived. of the pic i post. of every breath i take. and again, people ask me why. but i shut my mouth. i tell them i don’t know. i don’t tell them the truth because i’m ashamed. ashamed of you touching me. of you’re finger going inside of me. of your lips trying to get on mine. of me saying no. of you insisting. of me saying no again and again. and then, my mind wanted to die. wanted to see you die. see you die in horrible and sadic ways. just to see you hurting for the last 30 seconds of your life. why? because i’m ashamed of living my life suffering while you’re having fun with you’re little perfect life. and i could make you pay for that, but i’m ashamed to talk about it.

#metoo #rapevictim #shame
