victim blaming. so many times, when someone finally has the guts to step out of the shadow of guilt and tell her story of rape, the first reactions are: oh no, you should have done {insert action}. isn't that strange? should the first reaction anyone gives not be: "i'm so sorry this happened to you, let's go to the police?"
this further tells the victim that it was her fault.
•••○•••
this is what you get
when you walk home
all alone at night

this is what you get
for being afraid to
say “no” much louder

this is what you get
choosing to freeze in fear
over a kick in the nuts

this is what you get
if you face dominance
and let him have his way {swipe left}

text:
¿where did i go?
two days ago, i posted on my story saying that i was taking a couple days off social media to sort myself out. i feel like a two day breather was enough and i’m ready to talk about what happened. 
the best way to describe it is a kind of relapse/breakdown. after a few screwballs thrown at me in my personal life mainly my family, stress with university and not dealing with my own problems which impacted my relationship, i basically just couldn’t hack it. the best analogy was when you pull a stray thread on your t-shirt and it just keeps coming undone. i spent friday afternoon hysterical in tears or feeling like nothing. i had multiple calls with my well-being advisor who got me an emergency same day appointment with my gp. my well-being advisor talked me out of bed and i got dressed, which felt like the hardest task in the world, and i saw the doctor friday evening. on agreeing that my sertraline dose should be doubled (50mg to 100mg), due to tackling more shit since i began my medication, and being in a weird stage of limbo with waiting for therapy and waiting to carry on my transition, it had just been the last bad day to break the camel’s back. i got cleaned up and dressed by a nurse and then sorted myself out. i spent the evening with my girlfriend, who ran me a bath and took care of me, loving me even though i really didn’t care for myself. i took the time out to do things that make me happy such as bashing on the drums and starting a diary over the last few days. despite how bad it felt, the words of my girlfriend ring through my ears being that just because things are bad doesn’t mean it’s spiralling out of control. i need to start being independent and making myself happy and putting myself first. do shit like read, drum, write in my diaries, feel good things that make me happy. i am motivated to get back on top, and be active with my happiness. “happy’s not a destination man, it comes and goes” @laurensanderson - oceans🌊 
i love you guys, i’m sorry for going mia but i needed to take a breather to sort myself out. i need to change for me and the people i love, including all you folks. onwards and upwards💙✨🙇🏼‍♂️

the best way to describe it is a kind of relapse/breakdown. after a few screwballs thrown at me in my personal life mainly my family, stress with university and not dealing with my own problems which impacted my relationship, i basically just couldn’t hack it. the best analogy was when you pull a stray thread on your t-shi and it just keeps coming undone. i spent friday afternoon hysterical in tears or feeling like nothing. i had multiple calls with my well-being advisor who got me an emergency same day appointment with my gp. my well-being advisor talked me out of bed and i got dressed, which felt like the hardest task in the world, and i saw the doctor friday evening. on agreeing that my seraline dose should be doubled (50mg to 100mg), due to tackling more shit since i began my medication, and being in a weird stage of limbo with waiting for therapy and waiting to carry on my transition, it had just been the last bad day to break the camel’s back. i got cleaned up and dressed by a nurse and then soed myself out. i spent the evening with my girlfriend, who ran me a bath and took care of me, loving me even though i really didn’t care for myself. i took the time out to do things that make me happy such as bashing on the drums and staing a diary over the last few days. despite how bad it felt, the words of my girlfriend ring through my ears being that just because things are bad doesn’t mean it’s spiralling out of control. i need to sta being independent and making myself happy and putting myself first. do shit like read, drum, write in my diaries, feel good things that make me happy. i am motivated to get back on top, and be active with my happiness. “happy’s not a destination man, it comes and goes”  - oceans🌊 
i love you guys, i’m sorry for going mia but i needed to take a breather to so myself out. i need to change for me and the people i love, including all you folks. onwards and upwards💙✨🙇🏼‍♂️

text:
хочу обратиться к тем, кому "не нужен феминизм"

в этом посте я не буду писать о том, что феминизм уже дал женщинам. о праве получить образование, не быть собственностью отца/мужа, развестись (или не выходить замуж вовсе), о возможности не рожать десяток детей и не быть опозоренной за секс вне брака.

я хочу напомнить о безопасности. точнее, о её отсутствии. по данным воз, на протяжении жизни каждая третья женщина в мире становится жертвой физического или сексуального насилия. в большинстве случаев — со стороны партнёра-мужчины. каждая третья женщина. вдумайтесь в эти цифры. что, феминизм всё ещё не нужен?

вчера я рассказывала историю 2013 года о папе и гомофобии. сегодня хочу написать о том, что произошло чуть раньше. я смогла вытеснить воспоминания и не думала об этом случае до тех пор, пока не прогремели флешмобы "я не боюсь сказать" и "me too". сперва я читала истории, ужасалась и чувствовала облегчение от того, что со мной такого не происходило. а потом вспомнила.

историю можно прочитать в карусели.

мне очень тяжело дался пост. я никогда раньше об этом не упоминала. но я считаю, что насилие нельзя замалчивать. нужно говорить, чтобы те, кого это не коснулось, знали, что проблема есть.

а вы знали, что треть женщин подвергается насилию?
